    <section id="intro">
      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p>HTML is a markup language used to create static web pages and web applications. CSS is a style sheet language responsible for the presentation of documents written in a markup language.The main reason why HTML and CSS aren't considered programming languages is because they only determine the structure and the style of the webpage you're building.</p>
      
      <h2>How to create a website using HTML and CSS</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Step 1: Get a domain name and URL. It's important to choose a good domain name.</li>
  <li>Step 2: Set up an email address to match your domain name.</li>
  <li>Step 3: Find a web hosting company.</li>
  <li>Step 4: Design your website.</li>
  <li>Step 5: Build your website.</li>
  <li>Step 6: Add and manage your website content.</li>
  <li>Step 7: Publish your website.</li>
</ul>
      
    </section>
    <section id="porjects">
      <h2>Projects ideas</h2>
      <div class="project">
 
        
  <p>Certainly! Here's a list of friendly project ideas that you can create using HTML and CSS:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Personal Portfolio</strong>: Build a portfolio website to showcase your projects, skills, and experience. Include sections for your bio, projects, contact information, and a downloadable resume.</li>
    <li><strong>Recipe Book</strong>: Create a recipe website with your favorite recipes. Include images, ingredients, instructions, and maybe even some cooking tips.</li>
    <li><strong>Product Landing Page</strong>: Design a landing page for a fictional product or service. Include features, pricing, testimonials, and a call-to-action button.</li>
    <li><strong>Travel Destination Guide</strong>: Build a website showcasing your favorite travel destinations. Include photos, descriptions, maps, and recommendations for things to do.</li>
    <li><strong>Event Countdown Timer</strong>: Create a countdown timer for an upcoming event like a birthday, holiday, or vacation. Customize the design and include animations for added flair.</li>
    <li><strong>Tech Blog</strong>: Start a blog where you can write about technology news, reviews, and tutorials. Use CSS to style your posts and create a visually appealing layout.</li>
    <li><strong>Online Resume/CV</strong>: Design a digital resume or CV using HTML and CSS. Include sections for your education, work experience, skills, and achievements.</li>
    <li><strong>Weather App</strong>: Build a simple weather app that displays the current weather conditions for a specified location. Use CSS to style the interface and make it visually appealing.</li>
    <li><strong>Quiz or Trivia Game</strong>: Create a quiz or trivia game using HTML for the structure and CSS for styling. Include questions, multiple-choice answers, and a scoring system.</li>
    <li><strong>Personal Blog</strong>: Start a personal blog where you can write about your interests, hobbies, and experiences. Customize the design with CSS to reflect your personality.</li>
    <li><strong>Online Portfolio for Artists</strong>: Design a portfolio website for artists to showcase their artwork. Include galleries, descriptions, and contact information.</li>
    <li><strong>Fitness Tracker</strong>: Build a fitness tracker website where users can log their workouts, set goals, and track their progress. Use CSS to create a user-friendly interface.</li>
    <li><strong>Online Bookstore</strong>: Create a virtual bookstore with book covers, summaries, genres, and search functionality. Use CSS to style the layout and make it visually appealing.</li>
    <li><strong>Movie Database</strong>: Build a movie database website where users can search for movies, read reviews, and watch trailers. Use CSS to style the interface and make it user-friendly.</li>
    <li><strong>Music Player</strong>: Design a simple music player interface using HTML and CSS. Include controls for play, pause, skip, volume, and a playlist.</li>
  </ul>
      </div>
      <!-- Add more projects here -->
